OL,3,CPublic toilets under threat in
OL,4,CEastbourne as council tries to save
OL,5,Cmoney
OL,7,FThousands have signed a petition
OL,8,Fagainst closing public toilets on
OL,9,FEastbourne seafront, as campaigners
OL,10,Fsay they are an essential service that
OL,11,Fno one can do without.
OL,13,FEastbourne Council is consulting on
OL,14,Fplans to move towards a community
OL,15,Ftoilet scheme, to save money, and has
OL,16,Fonly committed to running one toilet
OL,17,Fon the seafront.
